title: How to Make Nachos – Sweet & Savory
description: These 2 nacho recipes will please both Team Savory and Team Sweet.

asset.author: Wilton
asset.description:
These 2 nacho recipes will please both Team Savory and Team Sweet.  
Get the printable how-to for Bacon Cheeseburger Nachos here: http://bit.ly/2cLvKsk 
Get the printable how-to for Birthday Cake Nachos here: http://bit.ly/2cADR6g 
Stay Sweet, Subscribe: http://s.wilton.com/10vmhuv
Bacon Cheeseburger Recipe:  
- Mega  Cookie Sheet - http://bit.ly/2cqo9Qu 
- 1 package (16 ounces) bacon (cut into 1/2” pieces)
- 1 1/4 pounds lean ground beef
- 1 tablespoon hamburger seasoning blend
- 1 package (16 ounces) tortilla chips
- 2 packages (8 ounces each) shredded cheddar jack cheese (divided)
- 1/2 cup diced Vidalia onion
- 2 cups shredded iceberg lettuce
- 1/2 cup prepared ranch dressing
- 1 1/2 cups diced roma Tomatoes (about 3 medium)
- peppers
- 1/2 cup drained sliced pickled jalapeno peppers
Birthday Cake Nachos Recipe: 
- Mega Cookie Sheet - http://bit.ly/2cqo9Qu 
- 1 package (12 ounces) Light Cocoa Candy Melts (melted according to package directions) - http://bit.ly/2ctPkqm 
- 1/2 cup Rainbow Jimmies (divided) - http://bit.ly/2ccIs2w 
- tortilla chips
- 2 bags (13 ounces each) salted tortilla chips (divided)
- 1 cup (2 sticks) butter, melted (divided)
- 1 package (15.25 ounces) white cake mix (divided)
- 1 package (8 ounces) thawed frozen whipped topping
